{
  "stem": "17761.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 17.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Steinberg, ?] Sholom Katz who was then cantor in Washington, and [NON-ENGLISH], who passed away in Israel, was cantor from [NON-ENGLISH] and so on and so on.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "All these figures, we had them there handy and without paying entry.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "So that was a total different thing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Then we had a cheder.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "There was in that place-- there was a school called [NON-ENGLISH], the Hebrew School, in which they studied at least partially in Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But that was a school recognized by the states.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But I didn't go to the [NON-ENGLISH] shul.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "It wasn't religious enough, so I went to the cheder.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And because of this, I never went even to public school.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "That was my-- my-- my studies were all in the religious area.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "We had a cheder in the courtyard of the temple of the place.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "There was a beautiful temple.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Of the temple?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The temple.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was no-- no name.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was der temple, or the das temple.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I don't remember.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I think the der temple, but maybe I'm wrong already.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And there we had a [NON-ENGLISH], a teacher.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I would like to mention his name, because he was a wonderful person and he perished also in Transnistria.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "His name was Rabbi Elimelach Fogel, F-O-G-E-L.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we studied there [NON-ENGLISH] and [NON-ENGLISH] and [NON-ENGLISH] and [NON-ENGLISH] and [NON-ENGLISH], you name it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And with my father, I started even [NON-ENGLISH], just because my father was an expert in this field.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the book I studied from is called [NON-ENGLISH] or [NON-ENGLISH], which was a famous book in this area.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Now, I used to play a lot.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I played soccer.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I was the goalkeeper usually, because I was probably very agile, so I could jump to catch the balls, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
